Code section

Ask some interesting question to the data, create hypothesis.¶

  • How many customer who has age 18-35 ?
  • What is the main issue for age 18-35 ?
  • Which assessment that most of age 18-35 takes ?
  • Why we focus on on this age range ?

Approach to the question¶

Feature description

The dataset contains customers answer to different vitality assessment.

There are 2 set of data

  • Raw data: It contains all the information required, one row contains only 1 customer attribute from an assessment.
  • Cleaned data: The data has been separated to 5 assessment files by the type of assessment the customer has done. In these 5 files, each row contains all the customer attributes from an assessment.

The datasets have 18154 assessments for 14007 customers

Assessment basic information

  • 'ENTITY_NO' System generated customer ID, even if the customer re-joined the
  • vitality program again after he left before, the ID should still be the same.
  • 'BUS_EFF_FROM' Customer vitality membership effective date
  • 'BUS_EFF_TO' Customer vitality membership expiry date, 31-Dec-99 means no specific expiry date
  • 'STAT_DESCR' Customer vitality membership level: Platinum, Gold, Silver, Bronze
  • 'CURR_PERIOD_START' Customer vitality point calculation cycle start date
  • 'TOT_POINTS' Customer accumulated vitality points from CURR_PERIOD_START
  • 'ASSESSMENT_SEQUENCE_NO' System generated assessment ID
  • 'CAPTURE_DATE' Date of assessment has been done
  • 'ASSESSMENT_GRP_ID' Assessment type ID
  • 'ASSESSMENT_GRP_DESCR' Assessment type description

Customers answers in assessments

  • 'attribute_67' Vitality age gap range, the difference between members Vitality age and actual age. Low less than 5 years difference; Med between 5 to 9 years difference; High 10 years or more difference.
  • For the other retributes, please refer to the assessment_attributes.csv in the folder

#gender
def ismale(col):
    if col == 'F':
        return 0
    else:
        return 1

def vagr(col):
    if col == 'Low':
        return 0
    elif col =='Medium':
        return 1
    elif col =='High':
        return 2
    else:
        return 0

df_stroke['VAGR'] = df_stroke['Vitality Age Gap Range'].apply(vagr)
